Fetch a user's age and determine a tier: *[tier is economics, not capability]*

```scheme
(cond
  ((< (loam/recall \"user-age\") 13) \"junior-tier\")
  ((< (loam/recall \"user-age\") 65) \"standard-tier\")
  (else \"senior-tier\"))
```

The age is fetched three times (each `cond` clause), and the tier string is returned. One form. (In practice, you might factor the recall out with `let`, but that's still one top-level form—Chapter 5 drills that collapse.)

